    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Indraprastha Apollo. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Senior Doctor to strengthen our Vijayawada-based team.\n\nAbout Indraprastha Apollo:\nIndraprastha Apollo is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Referral bonus program\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Indraprastha Apollo!",
